[[File:Rogue armour equipped.png|thumb|135px|A player wearing rogue armour.]]
'''Rogue equipment''' is an untradeable set of armour obtained from a [[rogue's equipment crate]], which are obtained from successfully opening the safes at the end of the [[Rogues' Den]] minigame. The set of clothing can be stored in an [[armour case]] within the [[costume room]] of a [[player-owned house]]. '''Note:''' as the pieces are untradeable, they will always be kept on death, except over level 20 wilderness. These items '''cannot''' be reclaimed from [[Perdu]].

While wearing pieces of the rogue armour, there is a chance of [[pickpocketing]] twice the loot from an [[NPC]], with the full set guaranteeing double loot. Each piece increases the chance of double loot by 20%.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1317554586077585410|date=17 October 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.md/C6y1o|archivedate=3 November 2021|quote=[Hey Ash, does each piece of rogue equipment give the same chance at doubling pickpocket loot?] They do.}} Experience drops remain unaffected.

The set effect does not affect stealing from chests, stalls, or activities such as Pyramid Plunder.

